items.label: The day you let one podcast run the table (and only played two songs)
items.detail: From sunrise to nightfall, you let “All-In with Chamath, Jason, Sacks & Friedberg” narrate nearly every hour—politics, AI, and poker took up almost the entire day. Only after dark did Rihanna and Slash break the streak with two quick tracks. 270 minutes, 1 podcast, 1 episode—your biggest podcast day of the year.

items.label: The day you let 133 artists crash your all-genre block party
items.detail: Overnight, you powered through the entire “Dear Evan Hansen” cast album, then let the morning drift from country to indie pop. By afternoon, jazz fusion, game soundtracks, and funk traded places, before evening spun through reggae, hyperpop, and orchestral detours. 454 minutes, 165 tracks, 133 artists—your widest-ranging listening marathon of the year.

items.label: The day you let “Habits (Stay High)” and “Often” loop the night away
items.detail: Afternoon launched with a Lady Gaga remix blitz, then the evening turned into a carousel of repeats: “Habits (Stay High)” and “Often” circled back again and again, with Kygo, Whitney Houston, and Tove Lo never far behind. 219 minutes, 135 plays, 33 repeated tracks—your most repeat-heavy day of the year.

items.label: The day you built a pop time machine from “Club Can't Handle Me” to “Story of My Life”
items.detail: Morning spun through fresh releases—Carly Rae Jepsen, Grimes, Quadeca—before the afternoon mellowed with Olēka and Carole King. By evening, you rewound to a “Club Can't Handle Me” radio marathon: Rihanna, Flo Rida, One Direction, and Pitbull stacked up nostalgia in every chorus. 200 minutes, 61 tracks, 73 artists—your most nostalgic day of the year.
